{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fdae508c-0c42-4392-b09d-161ccc4a49a9","content":"With xUnit v3 on MTP, the VSTest filter syntax (`~`, `&`) is replaced by MTP's own filter grammar. Here's the translation:\n\n**Old (VSTest):**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n**New (MTP):**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName contains IntegrationTests and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nKey differences:\n| VSTest | MTP |\n|--------|-----|\n| `~` (contains) | `contains` keyword |\n| `&` (and) | `and` keyword |\n| `=` (equals) | `=` (unchanged) |\n\nMTP also supports `or`, `not`, and parentheses for grouping. Trait filtering (`Category=Smoke`) works the same because xUnit v3 maps `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` to a filterable property named `Category`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"08b2df20-cf81-49cb-9a7a-19c2f683d3fe","outputTokens":234,"requestId":"BD0C:CDA86:1CFDD4A:20B49F2:6A07C58E"},"id":"75cbc53b-859d-4f24-9ec6-550b1727904f","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:17:12.205Z","parentId":"0f9372b9-fada-4733-8359-e2de7c0d2bde"}
